&lt;China Sports Service Corp> of China and&lt;Seylla Corp> of Hong Kong signed an agreement to borrow fivebillion yen from an international syndicate of banks led by theBank of China, the New China News Agency said.    It said the two firms will use the money to construct theOlympic Hotel, with 14 storeys and 380 rooms, near Peking'slargest indoor stadium, to cater for participants atinternational competitions and tourists.    Construction of the hotel is under way and due to becompleted by June 1988, the agency added but gave no moredetails. REUTER&#3;